comment: RHH shows Adams (OKC) lifts his knee and makes contact with Nowitzki on the start of his drive. A defender may position his leg between an offensive player's legs in the lower defensive box, but may not lift his foot from the floor and make contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) draws Kanter (OKC) into the air with pump fake. PBP angle shows no contact between shooter and defender and therefore no call.
After both players position for rebounding position, Adams (DAL) clamps and holds Chandler (DAL) after the ball hits the rim.
Roberson (OKC) sets a screen with his legs extended, however Rondo (DAL) goes around the screen and no illegal contact is made.
LATR shows Rondo (DAL) legally contests the jump shot by Westbrook (OKC) who spreads his leg in an attempt to create contact.
R-Slash shows Chandler (DAL) blocks the layup attempt by Kanter (OKC) before it touches the backboard.
Chandler (DAL) sets a screen on Waiters (OKC), giving him an opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Augustin (OKC) beats Parsons (DAL) to the point of contact on his drive to the basket.
R-Slash and LATR show Rondo (DAL) beats Westbrook (OKC) to the point of contact, and continues to retreat while covering him. Westbrook drives into Rondo.
R-Slash shows Westbrook (OKC) makes contact with Parsons (DAL), which prevents him from catching the pass.
Waiters (OKC) commits a take foul on Ellis (DAL).
McGary (OKC) commits a take foul on Ellis (DAL).
Kanter (OKC) commits a take foul on Jefferson (DAL).
Chandler (DAL) touches the net while contesting the layup attempt by Waiters (OKC), however, the contact does not cause the ball to make an unnatural bounce.
Waiters (OKC) commits a take foul on Ellis (DAL).
Kanter (OKC) sets the screen on Ellis (DAL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Rondo (DAL) remains inbounds as he saves the loose ball.
